>As human influence started to spread and anthro "pet" ownership was legalized, anthros started getting collared and tamed by human men with increasing frequency, even in the large previously anthro-only cities.
>Even though ownership required a consenting agreement or some other kind of legal rational, during this influx of human men moving in it wasn't uncommon for anthro girls to simply be snatched up in broad daylight, as some humans attempted to tame a girl with a good dicking first and worry about the legal semantics afterwards.
>Worried about this, some anthro girls (particularly the younger generation) resorted to an unusual tactic to avoid such a fate. Members of the Hunters Lodge (a respected human group comprised of those dedicated to the craft of hunting and claiming anthros) would sometimes offer their quarry an official Hunters lodge ear tag.
>These tags bore a unique ID code as well as the hunter's personal emblem, marking the anthro as their quarry. Everyone knew that such a tag meant a claim was staked, and even the humans not associated with the lodge would never interfere with another man's prey. This meant that the hunter would be able to pursue you at his own leisure, through whatever means he personally favored.
>Accepting a hunter's offer of a tag meant you could walk home from school safely and without worry... but came with a cost. Hunter's didn't hand such tags out frivolously, it meant that you were of special interest to them and that their would be no chance of waiting out their patience, shaking them off your trail. And all your friends, acquaintances, anyone who saw you with that tag clipped through your ear, would know. Know that you were being hunted, that you had caught the eye of some mysterious huntsman, and that you had reached a tentative but significant deal with him.
>That one day, almost inevitably, according to no one's time frame but his own... you'd be wearing his collar.
>And even though you weren't wearing one yet, having the promise of it clipped through your ear to mark you as spoken for prey was a seductive thing. And bearing that weight each day, thoughts drifting to scandalous possibilities as you wondered if you were at this very moment being watched, stalked by the apex predator that had marked you... it would begin to sow the seeds of domestication, without the hunter having to do a thing.

